    <h1>Equipment description</h1>
    <p>For optimal testing:

        Light masses (50kg): Any shaker could work, but Shaker 3 is most efficient Medium masses (50-150kg): Shaker 1
        would
        be ideal Heavy masses (>150kg): Only Shaker 2 would be suitable, especially at low frequencies
    </p>

    <p>
        Shaker 1 (Standard):

        Force: 25kN - Good for medium mass tests
        Displacement: 16mm - Adequate for most mid-frequency testing
        Best for: 50-200kg masses in 20-300Hz range

        Shaker 2 (Heavy Duty):

        Force: 35kN - Excellent for heavy mass testing
        Displacement: 25mm - Can handle low frequency, high displacement
        Best for: 100-300kg masses, especially at lower frequencies

        Shaker 3 (Compact):

        Force: 15kN - Limited to lighter masses
        Displacement: 12mm - More restricted in low frequency testing
        Best for: 50kg masses, higher frequency testing
    </p>
    <br>

    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html>
    <head>
        <title>Shaker Selection</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Select a Shaker</h1>
        <form action="/mssgs" method="POST">
            <div>
                <label>Select Shaker:</label>
                <select name="shaker" required>
                    <option value="shaker1">Standard Shaker - 25kN, 16mm</option>
                    <option value="shaker2">Heavy Duty Shaker - 35kN, 25mm</option>
                    <option value="shaker3">Compact Shaker - 15kN, 12mm</option>
                </select>
            </div>
            <button type="submit">Confirm choice</button>
        </form>
    </body>
    </html>
